{"apiVersion": "2024-11-30", "modelId": "prebuilt-layout", "stringIndexType": "textElements", "content": "For analyzing cell-cell communication in pathological tissues, we will use our physically Interacting Cells (PIC-seq) technology (Fig 3.42), providing us a detailed exploration circuits related to pathology and treatment response. Building upon the scRNA-seq data acquired in previous aims, we will isolate anticipated CART- immune/stromal cells PIC pairs from murine and patient blood and tissue samples, focusing on B cells and immune-stromal cells, such as synoviocytes in RA or epithelial glomerular cells in SLE, expressing BCMA43,44. In addition to PIC-seq, we will computationally model the interactome of cells utilizing NicheNet, a bioinformatic framework comprising a comprehensive database of ligand-receptor interactions and corresponding changes in downstream targets, to investigate cellular interactions45.\n", "pages": [{"pageNumber": 1, "words": [{"content": "For", "confidence": 1, "span": {"offset": 0, "length": 3}}, {"content": "analyzing", "confidence": 1, "span": {"offset": 4, "length": 9}}, {"content": "cell-cell", "confidence": 1, "span": {"offset": 14, "length": 9}}, {"content": "communication", "confidence": 1, "span": {"offset": 24, "length": 13}}, {"content": "in", "confidence": 1, "span": {"offset": 38, "length": 2}}, {"content": "pathological", "confidence": 1, "span": {"offset": 41, "length": 12}}, {"content": "tissues,", "confidence": 1, "span": {"offset": 54, "length": 8}}, {"content": "we", "confidence": 1, "span": {"offset": 63, "length": 2}}, {"content": "will", "confidence": 1, "span": {"offset": 66, "length": 4}}, {"content": "use", "confidence": 1, "span": {"offset": 71, "length": 3}}, {"content": "our", "confidence": 1, "span": {"offset": 75, "length": 3}}, {"content": "physically", "confidence": 1, "span": {"offset": 79, "length": 10}}, {"content": "Interacting", "confidence": 1, "span": {"offset": 90, "length": 11}}, {"content": "Cel